Reasoning: The article discusses the impact of the increase in the number of research articles indexed in the Web of Science database on the distribution of citations within these articles. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, given the focus on citation distributions and the use of physics articles as an example, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
